message: Hello! I found two main paths to success: 1. Use the 'vial' on a solid ingredient (mundane or magical) to create an extract. Then, combine a mundane liquid extract with a magical liquid (either another extract or a raw magical liquid like basilisk venom). This combination often results in a 100-value item directly. 2. Alternatively, combine a mundane liquid (raw or extracted) with a magical gas. This will often give a negative or low-value mixture initially, but then applying the 'filter' tool to this mixture will often result in a 100-value item. Avoid filtering solid ingredients, as this consistently led to negative-value, 'botched' items for me.

message: Hello! The most reliable strategy I found for a positive score (60 points) was to combine a 'magical gas' with a 'magical liquid'. Once you have this combined item, immediately use the 'filter' tool on it. Avoid using the 'vial' tool, as it consistently led to negative 'botched extraction' outcomes. Combining magical solid ingredients or any mundane ingredients rarely yielded positive results and often resulted in large negative values.
